Citation.sAbstract: The densities of (cyclohexanone +o-xylene, or m-xylene, or p-xylene) were measured at temperatures (293.15, 303.15, 313.15, 323.15, 333.15, 343.15, 353.15) K and atmospheric pressure by means of a vibrating-tube densimeter. The excess molar volume V calculated from the density data provide the temperature dependence of V in the temperature range of (293 to 353) K. The V  results were correlated using the fourth-order Redlich-Kister equation, with the maximum likelihood principle being applied for the determination of the adjustable parameters. It was found that the V  in the systems studied increase with rising temperature.
Citation.sTitle: Volumetric properties of (cyclohexanone + a xylene) at temperature between (293.15 and 353.15) K
